'*** PROGRAM: Demo how to use the PRINT command with numbers...

CLS '...(CL)ear the (O)utput screen window

'PRINT is used 2 different ways when it comes to printing out numbers...

'1> PRINT followed by the number itself...; 
'   this is also called printing 'numeric literals';
'   meaning printing the number, quite literally, 'as is'...

PRINT 2
'...output...
'2

'2> PRINT followed by a sum expression...;
'   the sum expression can be anything you choose: add(+)/subtact(-)/multiply(*)/divide(/), -etc.;
'   in this example we will use + plus...

PRINT 2 + 2
'...output...
'4

